[h1]Multiple Parameters[/h1]

You can define multiple parameters for a function by [b]comma-separating[/b] them. [code format="js"]function myFunc(x, y) {
   // some code
}[/code]
[note]The example above defines the function [b]myFunc [/b]to take two parameters.[/note]

quizzes.question:
What is the output of this code?
function test(x, y) {
  if(x>y) {
    document.write(x);
  }
  else {
    document.write(y);
  }
}
test(5, 8);

quizzes.textContent:
[h1]Multiple Parameters [/h1]

The parameters are used within the function's definition.[code format="js" ]function sayHello([b]name[/b], [b]age[/b]) {
  document.write( [b]name[/b] + " is " + [b]age[/b] + " years old.");
}[/code]

